			<div class="content" id="post-content-3689421">
									

<blockquote>
<p>My downvote fell right at the &quot;UIUseless&quot;, which elicited a heavy eyeroll.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yeah, I think that's where most of the other downvotes came from as well. Kalinin even mentioned it in the base article. The reason I did that is that I do think UIU were kind of useless in this scenario. They're unable to prevent the GOC from luring the Kaiju to 3ports, then demand they leave without cleaning up their mess, and then bring in MC&amp;D of all groups to haul off the corpse and don't charge them anywhere near enough for the privilege. I felt it would be well within Ruprecht's character to mock them for this.</p>
<p>I understand your reasons for downvoting and respect it, but I'm going to leave the line in.</p>
<p>I think you're right about this canon not reaching it's full potential. It's a wide-reaching event, sure, but so far it hasn't been that iconoclastic. It's just another anomaly for the GoIs to squabble over, albeit a really big one. Most of the authors for the canon haven't posted yet, so hopefully future works might go further into that.</p>

							</div>

								
					
