			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3689524">
									

<p>Because I apparently set myself up as a stawman with that line, I feel as though I should rephrase somewhat. That line by itself, while immersion-breaking enough to downvote at the point in which it appears, is not enough to write off the entire article, which could very well have been written well enough for me to change my mind.</p>
<p>What <em>cemented</em> my vote, to reiterate, is the barebones predictable plot. That there was some attempt at lampshading the obvious development (with the Sarkites) didn't do enough to make it an entertaining read. It's another article in the canon simply plugging group archetypes into articles, reinforcing the supposedly shaken status quo.</p>
<p>As an aside, unless the character is a former SH operative, I don't know why they'd refer to the GOC as 'bookburners', which is where that nickname originates from.</p>

