<blockquote>
<p>Practitioners of Sarkicism (or Sarkites) do not actually refer to themselves as &quot;Sarkic&quot; - the term a pejorative employed by the ancient Mekhanites<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-385543-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-385543-1')">1</a></sup> for their enemies. Thought to be their true name, it was adopted by the Global Occult Coalition and later by the Foundation as part of Project: Sitra Achra. In truth, Sarkic cultists refer to their belief system as <strong><em>Nälkä</em></strong><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-385543-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-385543-2')">2</a></sup></p>
</blockquote>
